Astrea of the Stars 15-Aug-21 04:26 PM
"Using vegetables from the garden, the fish are fed. Using nutrients from the fish, the vegetables are fed. This produces a cycle of almost limitless food, with only the need for water to be added."
That's what was on a plaque here as soon as you walked in the room. The room here is essentially a mini-garden of sorts - there's a huge raised platform in the middle, filled with plants - it forms a circle, with your OCs able to circle around the whole thing. I wouldn't suggest getting into it, though. The plants here seem to be in pipes of sorts that go across the entire platform - there's little holes in the pipes where the plants are able to be planted. Trying to get on top of the pipes would make you slip, falling into another set of pipes (ouch) or possibly even the pond just slightly underneath the plants. Yes, there is a little pond underneath the plants, though it's too hard to really make that out when it's covered by pipes. Looking into the pipes reveals that there are fishes swimming around, as happy as they can be. Water continuously flows into this 'pond' from somewhere else - you're not sure where, but it's probably best not to ask. Suggesting how you can reach into this place, your OC could destroy it (in a variety of ways) - though it would have disastrous consequences for everyone, including your OC. Please contact me if you still wish to do it, and only if it's after Chapter 2. (edited)
